    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MAYOR DEMANDS RESIGNATION</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By ELSA BRENNER</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mayor John D Spencer of Yonkers, NY, calls for his resignation after schools superintendent Andre J Hornsby blames city for school budget problems (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Mayor John D. Spencer of Yonkers is calling on Andre J. Hornsby, superintendent of schools, to quit, less than a year after he was hired. The mayor's comments followed a news conference by Dr. Hornsby on Tuesday, when he blamed the city for the schools' budget problems, which he said would mean cuts in programs and up to 1,000 layoffs. Dr. Hornsby, who has proposed a $353 million budget for the coming school year, said revenues fall $43 million short of expenses. ''I'm outraged that Dr. Hornsby made statements suggesting the city of Yonkers is not doing its part,'' Mr. Spencer said.</p>
        <p>ELSA BRENNER</p>
      </block>
